title: For Sale:  Enfield no. 2 "Tanker" Break-top Revolver
location: Highland / Metro East IL, St. Louis, Illinois
postcontent:
This is an old Enfield No. 2 Break-top revolver. The short barrel ones like this are often referred to as "tanker" or "pilot" models, but I am not guaranteeing it was ever in the hands of a tanker/pilot. Double Action with the spurred hammer, this is what the British forces replaced the old Webley with (if my research is correct) and shows a change in their entire approach to combat weapons.
It has a six round cylinder and fires .38 s&w. Shows signs of wear, but that's probably because it's a friggin old gun. Otherwise, it's clean and functional.
Asking $350, which seems to be far below the going rate if you can find one of these elsewhere. Not interested in trades, really, but will always entertain REASONABLE cash offers. Thank you.

title: For Sale:  Star Model S (.380acp)

postcontent:
Have up for sale a nifty little Star model S(s) .380acp pistol. The second 's' denotes one that has additional safeties, this one has a magazine safety as well as the thumb lever. It's built and comes apart almost exactly like a mini 1911, though the internal workings of the frame and trigger are not the same. I have put a box of Winchester ammo through it without issue.

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec PLR-16  +++
postcontent: Kel-tec is a gas-operated, semi-automatic pistol chambered in 5.56 NATO, manufactured by Kel-Tec Industries ofFlorida. The principal designer was George Kelgren, formerly of the the Intratec and Grendel firearms companies. The PLR (Pistol, Long Range) was designed for recreational target shooting, and small game, varmint, or predator hunting.[1] Due to the PLR’s relatively short barrel, the 5.56 cartridge’s velocity is considerably reduced compared to its velocity from a longer barrel. The PLR fires 55 grain ball ammunition 600fps slower than a 20″ barreled AR-15 rifle, and 300fps slower than a 14.5″ barreled M4 carbine. The PLR-16 combines the multi-lug rotating bolt design and breech-locking system of the AR-15 with a gas piston system similar to that of the M-1 Garand, M-14, and AK-47.[1] This system requires less maintenance than the direct gas impingement system of the AR-15 platform. The PLR-16’s frame is constructed of reinforced polymer, making the pistol both durable and light-weight. The frame incorporates an M-1913-style Picatinny rail molded to the top of the receiver to accept various optical sights.[1] Kel-Tec produces an optional polymer forend with a Picatinny rail for mounting flashlights or laser sights.This gun has it all!

This is a unique revolver, at some point was custom coated, it has been called french blued, or hard chromed, some have suggested it's Armaloy.  It is a beautiful look and each piece and part has been done.  The gun has had a trigger job by well known local gunsmith Wayne Lawhorn.(RIP)  It is a super smooth trigger pull.     Purchase includes a S&W Historical letter documenting that this was originally a Lew Horton, below is a copy of the specifics directly from the letter.  A serious S&W wheel gun collector would love to have this piece.  The finish has some shining wear under the cylinder and turnline, from normal use.  No box.

From S&W Letter(included in sale)

Your Model 29, .44 Magnum is part of a special order of five
thousand units with three inch barrels, round butt combat stocks
and a blue finish, which were originally produced for Lew Horton
Distributing Company with manufacturing of these handguns began
approximately July of 1985. However, Horton was not able to sell
all the units and requested Smith & Wesson to make them
available to other distributors.
We have researched your Model 29-3 .44 Magnum, Special Edition
Production, caliber .44 Remington Magnum, in our company
records. These records indicate that your revolver with serial
number ALA9XXX, was shipped from our factory on November 4,
1985, and delivered to Southern Gun Distributors Inc., Opa
Locka, FL. The records indicate that this firearm was shipped
wi th a 3 inch barrel, blue finish, and smooth Goncalo Alves
finger groove combat round butt grips.
I have several hundred rounds of .44 mag (Buffalo Bore, GA ARMS) that I will sell too.

The total extent of the interface is simply the take down pin, and the pivot pin. Your ARAK-21™ upper receiver will be shipped to you with one “Barrel Assembly Unit” (BAU), or two, depending on which package you purchase.
